						<summary>

						<p>On a slab in the Museum.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1475 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the grant of the village Voṟaur to Kēśavayya by Mādana <hi rend="italic">daṇḍanāyaka,</hi> in the presence of the god Nārāyaṇa of Hubbaḷi.</p>						

						<p>It is dated ś 1397, Jaya. Māgha, śu. 1. It corresponds to 1475 A.D., January 8, Sunday.</p>						

						</summary>
